%U A395169 4,6,6,5,1,3,0,5,8,0,7,0,9,1,3,0,8,4,9,9,3,6
%N A395169 Decimal expansion of the smallest dihedral angle, in radians, in an uniform 9-gonal antiprism.
%C A395169 This is the dihedral angle between a triangular face and a 9-gonal face.
%H A395169 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A395169/b395169.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395169 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Enneagonal_antiprism">Enneagonal antiprism</a>.
%H A395169 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Antiprism.html">Antiprism</a>.
%H A395169 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antiprism">Antiprism</a>.
%F A395169 Equals arccos(-tan(Pi/18)/sqrt(3)) = arccos(-A019908/A002194).
%F A395169 Equals arccos((cot(Pi/9) - csc(Pi/9))/sqrt(3)) = arccos((A019968 - A121602)/A002194).
%F A395169 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.101802... is the second smallest root of 9*(x^3 + x^2 - x) - 1.
%e A395169 1.67277542396835872275076810449100882923958460598689...
%t A395169 First[RealDigits[ArcCos[-Tan[Pi/18]/Sqrt[3]], 10, 100]]
%t A395169 (* Alternative: *)
%t A395169 First[RealDigits[Min[PolyhedronData["NonagonalAntiprism", "DihedralAngles"]], 10, 100]]
%Y A395169 Cf. A395170 (the other dihedral angle).
%Y A395169 Cf. A395164 (volume), A395165 (surface area), A395166 (midradius), A395167 (circumradius), A395168 (height).
%Y A395169 Cf. A002194, A019908, A019968, A121602.
